folder: Sea Breeze Avenue & 5th Street (West), Brooklyn, NY
text:
Sea Breeze Ave., between West 5th Street (left) and Ocean Parkway (right), looking northeast across Sea Side Park, showing the "Shelter House" at the northwest and the Brighton Theatre and the Peoples Bathing Pavilion at the
N.E. corners of Ocean Parkway and Sea Breeze Ave.
August 8, 1932.
P. L. Sperr.

folder: 5th Street (West) & Sea Breeze Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
text:
West 5th Street, west from nar[sic] Sea Breeze Avenue.
View 2 shows the first tow[sic] old buildings seen in view 1; They are right near the "El".
View 3 shows another old house.

P. L. Sperr
September 17, 1941
Views 1-3
